  "texts": [
    "• f time (A): Represents the time taken to execute the task, which must be minimized to enhance operational efficiency.",
    "This term is influenced by the Hamiltonian Path, which ensures the correct sequence of actions is followed to minimize delays.",
    "2) Determining the Weights: The weights α i in the objective function are determined based on the relative importance of each factor.",
    "For example, in tasks involving fragile objects, stability constraints may be prioritized over time efficiency.",
    "The weights are computed as:α i = 1 n n j=1 w j • I(constraint j),where:• w j: Importance of the j-th constraint, determined through domain knowledge, user preferences, and empirical data, • I(constraint j): Indicator function that returns 1 if the j-th constraint is active and 0 otherwise."
